Table.Name: wise_allskysc
Table.Description: Contains the parameters provided for each source in the WISE allsky catalogue

Column.Name: designation
Column.Description: Sexagesimal, equatorial position-based source name in the form: hhmmss.ss+ddmmss.s

Column.Name: ra
Column.Description: J2000 right ascension with respect to the 2MASS PSC reference frame.

Column.Name: dec
Column.Description: J2000 declination with respect to the 2MASS PSC reference frame.

Column.Name: sigra
Column.Description: One-sigma uncertainty in right ascension coordinate

Column.Name: sigdec
Column.Description: One-sigma uncertainty in declination coordinate

Column.Name: sigradec
Column.Description: The co-sigma of the equatorial position uncertainties, sig_ra, sig_dec (σ<sub>α</sub>, σδ<sub></sub>). The co-sigma is related to the covariance between the position errors Vαδ by the formula Vαδ = σ<sub>αδ</sub>×|σ<sub>αδ</sub>|. This maintains the sign information for the correlation, since σ<sub>αδ</sub> may be negative. It is more natural to carry the co-sigma along with the other uncertainties instead of the covariance because the former is in the same units as the other uncertainties.

Column.Name: glon
Column.Description: Galactic longitude. CAUTION: This coordinate should not be used as an astrometric reference.

Column.Name: glat
Column.Description: Galactic latitude. CAUTION: This coordinate should not be used as an astrometric reference.

Column.Name: elon
Column.Description: Ecliptic longitude. CAUTION: This coordinate should not be used as an astrometric reference.

Column.Name: elat
Column.Description: Ecliptic latitude. CAUTION: This coordinate should not be used as an astrometric reference.

Column.Name: wx
Column.Description: The x-pixel coordinate of this source on the Atlas Image.

Column.Name: wy
Column.Description: The y-pixel coordinate of this source on the Atlas Image.

Column.Name: cntr
Column.Description: Unique identification number for the Catalog source

Column.Name: source_id
Column.Description: Unique source ID, formed from a combination of the Atlas Tile ID, coadd_id, and sequential extracted source number, src, within the Tile.

Column.Name: coadd_id
Column.Description: Atlas Tile identifier from which source was extracted.

Column.Name: src
Column.Description: Sequential number of this source extraction in the Atlas Tile from which this source was extracted, in approximate descending order of W1 source brightness.

Column.Name: w1mpro
Column.Description: W1 magnitude measured with profile-fitting photometry, or the magnitude of the 95% confidence brightness upper limit if the W1 flux measurement has SNR<2.

Column.Name: w1sigmpro
Column.Description: W1 profile-fit photometric measurement uncertainty.

Column.Name: w1snr

Column.Name: w1rchi2

Column.Name: w2mpro

Column.Description: W3 magnitude of source measured in the elliptical aperture described by w3rsemi, w3ba, and w3pa

Column.Name: w3gerr
Column.Description: Uncertainty in the W3 magnitude of source measured in elliptical aperture

Column.Name: w3gflg
Column.Description: W3 elliptical aperture measurement quality flag

Column.Name: w4rsemi
Column.Description: Semi-major axis of the elliptical aperture used to measure source in W4

Column.Name: w4ba
Column.Description: Axis ratio (b/a) of the elliptical aperture used to measure source in W4

Column.Name: w4pa
Column.Description: Position angle (degrees E of N) of the elliptical aperture major axis used to measure source in W4

Column.Name: w4gmag
Column.Description: W4 magnitude of source measured in the elliptical aperture described by w4rsemi, w4ba, and w4pa

Column.Name: w4gerr
Column.Description: Uncertainty in the W4 magnitude of source measured in elliptical aperture

Column.Name: w4gflg
Column.Description: W4 elliptical aperture measurement quality flag

Column.Name: tmass_key
Column.Description: Unique identifier of the closest source in the 2MASS Point Source Catalog (PSC) that falls within 3" of the position of this WISE source

Column.Name: r_2mass
Column.Description: Distance separating the positions of the WISE source and associated 2MASS PSC source within 3", default if there is no associated 2MASS PSC source

Column.Name: pa_2mass
Column.Description: Position angle (degrees E of N) of the vector from the WISE source to the associated 2MASS PSC source, default if there is no associated 2MASS PSC source

Column.Name: n_2mass
Column.Description: The number of 2MASS PSC entries found within a 3" radius of the WISE source position

Column.Name: j_m_2mass
Column.Description: 2MASS J-band magnitude or magnitude upper limit of the associated 2MASS PSC source

Column.Name: j_msig_2mass
Column.Description: 2MASS J-band corrected photometric uncertainty of the associated 2MASS PSC source

Column.Name: h_m_2mass
Column.Description: 2MASS H-band magnitude or magnitude upper limit of the associated 2MASS PSC source

Column.Name: h_msig_2mass
Column.Description: 2MASS H-band corrected photometric uncertainty of the associated 2MASS PSC source

Column.Name: k_m_2mass
Column.Description: 2MASS Ks-band magnitude or magnitude upper limit of the associated 2MASS PSC source

Column.Name: k_msig_2mass
Column.Description: 2MASS Ks-band corrected photometric uncertainty of the associated 2MASS PSC source

Column.Name: cx
Column.Description: unit vector of spherical co-ordinates (similar to x in IPAC IRSA schema, but recomputed)

Column.Name: cy
Column.Description: unit vector of spherical co-ordinates (similar to y in IPAC IRSA schema, but recomputed)

Column.Name: cz
Column.Description: unit vector of spherical co-ordinates (similar to z in IPAC IRSA schema, but recomputed)

Column.Name: htmID
Column.Description: Hierarchical Triangular Mesh (HTM) index for equatorial co-ordinates (similar to spt_ind in IPAC IRSA schema, but recomputed to level 20)
